# WEB ATELIER (UDIT) - AI Assistant Rules for Student Projects

## Project Context

This is a student web development project for the WEB ATELIER (UDIT) course. Students are learning modern web development with a focus on:

- Semantic HTML5
- Modern CSS (Grid, Flexbox, Custom Properties)
- Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+)
- Accessibility (WCAG AA compliance)
- Performance optimization
- Progressive enhancement
- Responsive design (mobile-first)

## Code Style & Standards

### HTML

- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`)
- Always include proper document structure with `<!DOCTYPE html>`, `<html lang="es">` or `lang="en"`
- Include essential meta tags: `charset`, `viewport`, `description`
- Use ARIA attributes when needed for accessibility (`aria-label`, `aria-labelledby`, `role`)
- Add `alt` text to all images
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3, no skipping levels)
- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation
- Include skip links for keyboard navigation: `<a href="#main" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>`

**Example:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="es">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<meta name="description" content="Student portfolio showcasing web design projects" />
		<title>My Portfolio - WEB ATELIER</title>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="./assets/css/style.css" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<a href="#main" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>

		<header>
			<nav aria-label="Main navigation">
				<ul>
					<li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
					<li><a href="#projects">Projects</a></li>
					<li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
				</ul>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main id="main">
			<section id="about">
				<h1>About Me</h1>
				<p>Welcome to my portfolio...</p>
			</section>
		</main>

		<footer>
			<p>&copy; 2025 Student Name - WEB ATELIER (UDIT)</p>
		</footer>

		<script src="./assets/js/main.js"></script>
	</body>
</html>
```

### CSS

- Use CSS Custom Properties (variables) for design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
- Follow mobile-first responsive design approach
- Use modern layout techniques: CSS Grid for page layouts, Flexbox for components
- Implement fluid typography with `clamp()` for responsive font sizes
- Use semantic class names (BEM methodology optional but recommended)
- Ensure WCAG AA color contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- Support dark mode with `prefers-color-scheme` media query
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for accessibility
- Use logical properties when appropriate (`margin-inline`, `padding-block`)

**Example:**

```css
:root {
	/* Design tokens */
	--color-primary: #1d4ed8;
	--color-text: #0f172a;
	--color-bg: #ffffff;

	--font-size-base: clamp(1rem, 0.8vw + 0.85rem, 1.125rem);
	--space-md: 1rem;

	--transition-base: 250ms ease-in-out;
}

/* Dark mode support */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
	:root {
		--color-text: #f1f5f9;
		--color-bg: #0f172a;
	}
}

/* Mobile-first approach */
.container {
	padding: var(--space-md);
}

/* Tablet and up */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
	.container {
		padding: var(--space-lg);
	}
}

/* Accessibility: respect motion preferences */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
	* {
		animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
		transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
	}
}
```

### JavaScript

- Use modern ES6+ syntax (const/let, arrow functions, template literals, destructuring)
- Avoid jQuery - use vanilla JavaScript
- Use `addEventListener` instead of inline event handlers
- Implement progressive enhancement (site works without JS)
- Use `defer` or place scripts at end of `<body>`
- Add meaningful comments explaining "why", not "what"
- Handle errors gracefully with try/catch
- Use `querySelector` and `querySelectorAll` for DOM selection
- Prefer `fetch` API over XMLHttpRequest

**Example:**

```javascript
// Wait for DOM to be ready
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
	// Smooth scroll for anchor links
	const links = document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="#"]');

	links.forEach((link) => {
		link.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
			e.preventDefault();
			const targetId = link.getAttribute('href').substring(1);
			const target = document.getElementById(targetId);

			if (target) {
				target.scrollIntoView({
					behavior: 'smooth',
					block: 'start',
				});
			}
		});
	});

	// Dark mode toggle
	const darkModeToggle = document.querySelector('[data-theme-toggle]');

	if (darkModeToggle) {
		darkModeToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
			document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark-mode');
			const isDark = document.documentElement.classList.contains('dark-mode');
			localStorage.setItem('theme', isDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
		});
	}

	// Load saved theme preference
	const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme');
	if (savedTheme === 'dark') {
		document.documentElement.classList.add('dark-mode');
	}
});
```

## Performance Best Practices

- Optimize images (use WebP format, compress, lazy load)
- Minimize CSS and JavaScript files for production
- Use `preload` for critical resources
- Implement lazy loading for images: `<img loading="lazy" />`
- Avoid layout shifts (CLS) by specifying image dimensions
- Use `font-display: swap` for web fonts
- Minimize HTTP requests
- Target Lighthouse scores: 90+ for Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices, SEO

**Example:**

```html
<!-- Preload critical resources -->
<link rel="preload" href="./assets/css/style.css" as="style" />
<link rel="preload" href="./assets/fonts/main-font.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin />

<!-- Optimized image with lazy loading -->
<img
	src="./images/hero-image.webp"
	alt="Portfolio hero image"
	width="1200"
	height="600"
	loading="lazy"
	decoding="async"
/>
```

## Accessibility Requirements

- Maintain proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Provide text alternatives for images (`alt` attributes)
- Ensure keyboard navigation works (test with Tab key)
- Use ARIA labels for icon-only buttons
- Maintain 4.5:1 contrast ratio for text
- Support screen readers with semantic HTML
- Include skip links for keyboard users
- Test with keyboard only (no mouse)
- Ensure focus indicators are visible

**Example:**

```html
<!-- Icon button with accessible label -->
<button aria-label="Toggle dark mode" class="theme-toggle">
	<svg aria-hidden="true" width="24" height="24">
		<use href="#icon-moon"></use>
	</svg>
</button>

<!-- Form with proper labels -->
<form>
	<label for="email">Email Address</label>
	<input type="email" id="email" name="email" required aria-required="true" />

	<label for="message">Your Message</label>
	<textarea id="message" name="message" required aria-required="true"></textarea>

	<button type="submit">Send Message</button>
</form>
```

