## What NOT to Do

- ❌ Don't use inline styles (`style="..."`)
- ❌ Don't use `!important` unless absolutely necessary
- ❌ Don't use deprecated HTML elements (`<center>`, `<font>`)
- ❌ Don't rely on JavaScript for critical functionality
- ❌ Don't use `div` when semantic elements exist
- ❌ Don't skip heading levels (h1 → h3)
- ❌ Don't use generic class names (`div1`, `box`, `container1`)
- ❌ Don't forget `alt` text on images
- ❌ Don't use fixed pixel values for fonts (use rem/em)
- ❌ Don't ignore mobile devices (always test responsive)

## Testing Checklist

Before each commit, verify:

- [ ] HTML validates (use W3C validator)
- [ ] CSS validates (use W3C CSS validator)
- [ ] No JavaScript console errors
- [ ] Works on mobile (320px width minimum)
- [ ] Works on tablet (768px)
- [ ] Works on desktop (1920px)
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works (Tab, Enter, Escape)
- [ ] Screen reader friendly (test with NVDA/JAWS/VoiceOver)
- [ ] Color contrast passes WCAG AA
- [ ] Images have alt text
- [ ] Links have descriptive text (not "click here")
- [ ] Forms have proper labels

